Jenna Etheridge, News24(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; Three men have yet to be arrested after shooting and wounding a Belhar man on Wednesday afternoon, Western Cape police said.The unidentified men fired shots in Chestnut Way around noon before fleeing the scene, said Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana.The 27-year-old man was shot in the chest, arms and legs, added provincial government health EMS spokesperson Robert Daniels.He was rushed to hospital in critical condition.A case of attempted murder has been opened.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.